This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a matrix completion approach for detecting unorganized malicious attacks in recommender systems. It may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. Additionally, since the paper deals with attack detection, it may belong to the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper's focus on recommender systems may also make it relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, since the proposed approach involves optimization techniques, it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
